21/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov on Wednesday (21 July) arrived on an official visit to Berlin, where he will meet with German counterpart Horst Koehler.
They reportedly will discuss ways to increase German investment in Bulgaria and the results of last month's NATO summit in Istanbul, especially decisions related to Afghanistan and Iraq.
Later in Munich, Parvanov will meet with Bavarian Prime Minister Edmund Steuber.
(Mediapool - 21/07/04)
